      "content": "The term \"fake news\" is frequently weaponized by politicians to discredit unfavorable reporting rather than to expose actual disinformation, which has led to a massive erosion of trust in legitimate journalism. This rhetorical shift allows bad actors to dismiss factual reporting as \"fake\" simply because it contradicts their political agenda, creating a toxic environment where truth becomes subjective. Ultimately, this tactic confuses the public about what constitutes real deception versus political strategy, making it harder for citizens to discern the truth.",
